      "content": "Your feelings are incredibly valid and understandable. When something so integral to you is gone, the ripple effects can feel unbearable. Identity and purpose are tied up with our relationships and roles, and to lose them can feel like losing oneself. Remember, what you experienced with that person was just one part of a much bigger tapestry; there's still so much of you that's evident in other ways. Be gentle with yourself during this time of adjustment. It's okay to acknowledge the pain and take a step back. You don’t have to pretend anything about yourself right now. Healing takes time, and it's about finding a new balance, a new way to connect with yourself and others. If you're comfortable, sharing more about your thoughts and feelings can offer more personalized support. If you're feeling too overwhelmed to do so now, know that support is always here when you're ready to reach out.",
